[SN]TITLE[SN]
Driver injured after car comes off road in Midlothian

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been seriously injured after his car came off the road and was discovered in a wooded area in Midlothian.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police said the crash happened on the A6094 between Howgate and Rosewell.
The heavily damaged Honda Civic was discovered by another motorist at about 07:30 on Saturday. The 27-year-old driver is being treated in hospital.
Officers have appealed for any witnesses to contact them.
